The numbers are arranged on a hexagonal lattice in a spiral.  
For a point with hex‑axial coordinates \((q,r)\) the “hex‑distance’’ (the ring number) is  

\[
R=\max\bigl(|q|,\;|r|,\;|{-q-r}|\bigr).
\]

For the ring \(R\) the smallest number on the ring is  

\[
N_{\text{start}} = 2+3R(R-1)
\]

and the numbers are written, starting at the point \((R,0)\), moving along the six edges

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{edge }0 &: (R-i,\,-i) \qquad i=0\ldots R-1\\
\text{edge }1 &: (-i,\,-R)\\
\text{edge }2 &: (-R,\,-R+i)\\
\text{edge }3 &: (-R+i,\,i)\\
\text{edge }4 &: (i,\,R-i)\\
\text{edge }5 &: (R,\,i)
\end{aligned}
\]

If a point lies on edge‑\(e\) with index \(i\) (counting from \(0\)), its value is  

\[
N = N_{\text{start}} + \bigl(eR+i\bigr).
\]

---

### 1.  Coordinates of 2026  

The ring that contains 2026 is obtained from  

\[
3R(R+1)+1\ge 2026 \Longrightarrow R=26 .
\]

The first number of this ring is  

\[
N_{\text{start}}=2+3\cdot26\cdot25 = 1952 .
\]

The offset of 2026 is \(2026-1952 = 74\).  
Since each edge has length \(26\),

\[
74 = 2\cdot 26 + 22,
\]

so 2026 is on **edge 2** (\(q=-R\)) with \(i=22\).  
Hence its axial coordinates are  

\[
(q,r)=(-26,\,-26+22)=(-26,-4).
\]

---

### 2.  The six neighbours  

Adding the six neighbour‑vectors  

\[
(-1,-1),\;(-1,0),\;(0,1),\;(1,1),\;(1,0),\;(0,-1)
\]

to \((-26,-4)\) gives  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-27,-5),\;(-27,-4),\;(-26,-3),\;(-25,-3),\;(-25,-4),\;(-26,-5).
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3.  Convert each neighbour back to its number  

| coordinate \((q,r)\) | ring \(R\) | edge / index \(i\) | number |
|----------------------|-----------|-------------------|--------|
| \((-27,-5)\) | 27 | edge 2, \(i=22\) | \(2+3\cdot27\cdot26 + 2\cdot27 + ( -5+27)=2108+76 = 2184\) |
| \((-27,-4)\) | 27 | edge 2, \(i=23\) | \(2108+77 = 2185\) |
| \((-26,-3)\) | 26 | edge 2, \(i=23\) | \(1952+75 = 2027\) |
| \((-25,-3)\) | 25 | edge 2, \(i=22\) | \(1802+72 = 1874\) |
| \((-25,-4)\) | 25 | edge 2, \(i=21\) | \(1802+71 = 1873\) |
| \((-26,-5)\) | 26 | edge 2, \(i=21\) | \(1952+73 = 2025\) |

---

### 4.  Sum of the six neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{sum}&= 2184+2185+2027+1874+1873+2025 \\
&= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
